1
00:00:04,334 --> 00:00:05,334
Andres!

2
00:00:05,834 --> 00:00:09,292
Move faster! Our grand
launch is about to start!

3
00:00:10,083 --> 00:00:11,083
Yes, Dad!

4
00:00:11,709 --> 00:00:13,834
Tash, everyone’s rushing outside
and yet you’re still dancing!

5
00:00:14,775 --> 00:00:15,791
Hello?!

6
00:00:15,815 --> 00:00:19,692
I’m practicing my
performance for later!

7
00:00:19,941 --> 00:00:22,442
So we’re sure to
have entertainment!

8
00:00:22,775 --> 00:00:23,834
That’s all good, move faster!

9
00:00:23,858 --> 00:00:24,858
What are you trying
to do to me?!

10
00:00:25,899 --> 00:00:27,959
What are you doing?
This is what I’ve been saying,

11
00:00:27,983 --> 00:00:29,941
you look like you’ve
got no sense of urgency!

12
00:00:30,275 --> 00:00:31,791
And you, what’s with
all the dancing?!

13
00:00:31,815 --> 00:00:35,483
Dad, you’re all misconceptions.

14
00:00:35,815 --> 00:00:39,775
I’m not just dancing,
this is much more than that!

15
00:00:39,815 --> 00:00:42,910
What do you mean it’s much more than that,
look at you all dancey-dance!

16
00:00:43,734 --> 00:00:44,834
What does kendeng mean?

17
00:00:44,858 --> 00:00:45,858
What does that mean?

18
00:00:45,883 --> 00:00:49,400
Kendeng-kendeng
means dancey-dance!

19
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:50,815
You’re all dancey-dance!

20
00:00:51,983 --> 00:00:52,983
Kendeng

21
00:00:53,815 --> 00:00:56,459
you look like a girly-girl!

22
00:00:56,483 --> 00:01:01,191
Hey! Just because I swish
my hips well, I’m a girly-girl!

23
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,400
What are you saying?

24
00:01:02,815 --> 00:01:04,815
You’re all misconceptions!

25
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:07,316
Okay, so here’s the thing.

26
00:01:08,066 --> 00:01:13,150
Speaking of misconceptions,
this is our story for today.

27
00:02:14,815 --> 00:02:16,459
- Boss Beauty!
- Yes?

28
00:02:16,483 --> 00:02:18,983
Can you maybe lend me
eggs and flour?

29
00:02:19,442 --> 00:02:20,791
Get them some eggs and flour.

30
00:02:20,815 --> 00:02:21,875
Yo! Move faster,
you might not catch up to us here!

31
00:02:21,899 --> 00:02:22,899
It’s here!

32
00:02:24,014 --> 00:02:25,041
What’s happening over there?

33
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:27,129
- You really wanna know?
- Okay, tell me.

34
00:02:27,403 --> 00:02:28,543
- It’s like this.
- Okay?

35
00:02:30,038 --> 00:02:31,038
The…

36
00:02:31,046 --> 00:02:32,046
The what?

37
00:02:32,088 --> 00:02:35,081
there are people who transferred…

38
00:02:35,106 --> 00:02:36,106
Okay…?

39
00:02:36,623 --> 00:02:37,623
And?

40
00:02:37,938 --> 00:02:39,938
They’re running an illegal business.

41
00:02:40,601 --> 00:02:42,728
Okay, go on… go on…
Boss Beauty…

42
00:02:43,157 --> 00:02:44,230
What is that, Boss Beauty?

43
00:02:44,255 --> 00:02:47,173
You can just text it to me,
you don’t have to come close to me.

44
00:02:47,822 --> 00:02:49,245
- Just so it’s clear.
- Right, right. And also…

45
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,083
We’re causing a scene.
What is it, what is it?

46
00:02:51,108 --> 00:02:52,680
we already knew
about that, didn’t we?

47
00:02:53,137 --> 00:02:56,414
That there’s an illegal business
being run by our neighbors?

48
00:02:56,439 --> 00:02:57,811
What, what, say that again?
I can’t hear. What?

49
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:00,646
Our new neighbors
at the end of the street…

50
00:03:00,671 --> 00:03:04,512
- What happened?
- run an illegal business.

51
00:03:04,537 --> 00:03:08,056
- Where?
- Down there! Our new neighbors!

52
00:03:08,081 --> 00:03:09,591
I thought you
could have texted it?

53
00:03:09,616 --> 00:03:12,677
Oh just shut up, he’s saying something.
He’s saying something!

54
00:03:12,702 --> 00:03:15,484
- Let me say it, let me say it!
- No, not you! Let him do it!

55
00:03:15,509 --> 00:03:17,713
- I know it better…
- I said no! No! It’s fine!

56
00:03:17,738 --> 00:03:19,188
- No!
- You don’t like me?

57
00:03:19,213 --> 00:03:20,638
No, it’s fine! Come here…

58
00:03:20,885 --> 00:03:22,065
Illegal, is there something illegal?

59
00:03:22,597 --> 00:03:24,714
Don’t judge the people.

60
00:03:24,739 --> 00:03:28,272
If the business is good, then it’s fine.

61
00:03:28,657 --> 00:03:30,297
You don’t need to be jealous about it.

62
00:03:30,956 --> 00:03:33,843
If the business is good,
it makes it good, then let them be.

63
00:03:33,868 --> 00:03:36,388
Pervert! Pervert!

64
00:03:39,859 --> 00:03:40,859
Pervert!

65
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:42,377
- Pervert!
- Hey! What’s happening?!

66
00:03:42,402 --> 00:03:43,721
There’s a peeping tom there!

67
00:03:43,894 --> 00:03:45,760
A peeping pervert?!
Where?! Who?!

68
00:03:46,182 --> 00:03:48,302
All of them!
Look at them running like rats!

69
00:03:53,602 --> 00:03:55,244
- What happened?!
- Oh…

70
00:03:55,269 --> 00:03:59,206
- There’s a peeping pervert!
- I was just… waiting for Andres… he’s…

71
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,304
- Were you the peeping perverts?!
- No! No, we aren’t!

72
00:04:01,329 --> 00:04:03,737
- No, no, no!
- Look, they all ran…

73
00:04:03,762 --> 00:04:07,818
No, don’t believe them… they…
they went that way! They were peeping!

74
00:04:07,843 --> 00:04:09,188
- It wasn’t us!
- No, it wasn’t!

75
00:04:09,213 --> 00:04:10,506
But you were a part of them!

76
00:04:10,612 --> 00:04:14,838
I would never peep!
Bold of you to accuse me!

77
00:04:14,863 --> 00:04:17,411
Andres! See!
Look at what’s happening to you!

78
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:18,879
Cap!

79
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:20,714
Easy, easy! Don’t go too fast!

80
00:04:22,413 --> 00:04:23,486
But… there’s a peeper, isn’t there?

81
00:04:23,511 --> 00:04:26,124
Yes, Cap! These people are peepers!

82
00:04:26,149 --> 00:04:27,838
- It wasn’t us, Kap!
- No, no!

83
00:04:27,863 --> 00:04:29,419
- Then, who?!
- I have no idea,

84
00:04:29,443 --> 00:04:30,620
I just saw people running…

85
00:04:30,789 --> 00:04:32,842
And you want me to believe that?
Take them to the barangay hall!

86
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:35,214
Wait, wait, why are you taking us!
We weren’t the ones peeping!

87
00:04:35,246 --> 00:04:39,093
Well, this is your son! Just go with them,
I’ll take care of Cap!

88
00:04:39,118 --> 00:04:40,186
- Go, go!
- Go, now!

89
00:04:40,211 --> 00:04:42,509
What, why are we
suddenly the peepers?!

90
00:04:42,827 --> 00:04:47,081
I was just asking the questions,
I wanted to help, and now I’m the peeper?!

91
00:04:47,538 --> 00:04:50,018
You know, that father and son tandem
are really peepers!

92
00:04:50,690 --> 00:04:52,237
You can’t really trust them!

93
00:04:52,405 --> 00:04:55,231
I’ll take you to the Barangay Hal.

94
00:04:56,684 --> 00:04:59,212
- Cap, Cap!
- Cap! Wait up!

95
00:04:59,609 --> 00:05:03,871
Ma’am Alice, I’m so sorry for
what my Dad and my Kuya did.

96
00:05:04,574 --> 00:05:06,741
Your daddy? I wasn’t one of them!

97
00:05:07,029 --> 00:05:09,104
Tash, I wasn’t one of the peepers,

98
00:05:09,128 --> 00:05:11,461
I don’t have anything to apologize for,
I didn’t peep!

99
00:05:11,595 --> 00:05:12,718
Me, too!

100
00:05:12,742 --> 00:05:14,247
Kuya Iskineport just
called me over,

101
00:05:14,436 --> 00:05:16,216
and told me he was going to
introduce me to someone.

102
00:05:16,251 --> 00:05:17,811
- Oh. Introduce?
- Yeah.

103
00:05:17,844 --> 00:05:19,019
But she was in the shower.

104
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:21,263
Is it our fault that
she takes too long to shower?

105
00:05:21,293 --> 00:05:23,005
When I came over to
introduce Andres,

106
00:05:23,029 --> 00:05:24,728
she was still taking a shower,
then it’s your fault!

107
00:05:24,753 --> 00:05:26,532
- You apologize to us!
- What?!

108
00:05:26,557 --> 00:05:27,772
Okay, wait up, wait up.

109
00:05:27,797 --> 00:05:30,369
I’m sure this is all just
a misunderstanding!

110
00:05:31,236 --> 00:05:32,603
I’m Chacha,

111
00:05:32,792 --> 00:05:37,552
this is Aga, my husband, and these are
my children, Atasha, and Andres.

112
00:05:37,577 --> 00:05:39,295
And this is… Iskineport.

113
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:40,868
- Iskineport.
- Iskineport is your son, too?

114
00:05:40,893 --> 00:05:42,024
Oh, no, he isn’t.

115
00:05:42,049 --> 00:05:43,831
I thought you were gonna say Iskineport
is your son, too. He’s our oven operator.

116
00:05:43,856 --> 00:05:45,279
Oven operator.

117
00:05:45,758 --> 00:05:49,752
Oh, I see. My name is Alicia Poe-Go.

118
00:05:50,094 --> 00:05:52,094
Hi, Alicia! Hello.

119
00:05:52,119 --> 00:05:54,486
Hello! Let me ask you something, Alicia.

120
00:05:54,511 --> 00:05:56,412
You just sprouted out
of here all of a sudden.

121
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,100
Where are you from?

122
00:05:58,125 --> 00:05:59,125
Um,

123
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,666
I grew up on a farm.

124
00:06:04,527 --> 00:06:09,761
I grew up hidden from the world,
that’s why I’m really shy.

125
00:06:11,545 --> 00:06:13,365
Chef K is my godfather, actually.

126
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:14,516
- What?!
- Oh!

127
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,018
Chef K, Alice is your goddaughter?

128
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:18,273
Uh, yeah.

129
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:24,624
Do you remember that car show
when I brought with me a BaklaRen620?

130
00:06:25,825 --> 00:06:26,852
What, BaklaRen?!

131
00:06:26,877 --> 00:06:28,262
Yeah, BaklaRen!

132
00:06:28,981 --> 00:06:30,448
That was hers, I just borrowed it.

133
00:06:31,034 --> 00:06:34,041
So there, to return the favor,

134
00:06:34,371 --> 00:06:38,565
I found her a place here in
our barangay for her business.

135
00:06:38,650 --> 00:06:40,701
What’s your business?

136
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:44,004
I can’t remember anything, your honor.

137
00:06:44,558 --> 00:06:45,587
Hey!

138
00:06:45,612 --> 00:06:47,474
You know I was an honor
student back in elementary?!

139
00:06:47,515 --> 00:06:48,742
You’re good!

140
00:06:48,803 --> 00:06:50,210
Don’t answer.

141
00:06:50,212 --> 00:06:52,713
He doesn’t make sense.

142
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,759
I can see that.

143
00:06:53,793 --> 00:06:55,495
But you’re swinging the
topic to a different direction!

144
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,592
- Why?
- I saw you two!

145
00:06:57,887 --> 00:06:59,386
You were peeping!

146
00:07:00,599 --> 00:07:02,623
I wasn’t! It wasn’t…

147
00:07:02,637 --> 00:07:07,024
Um, Alice, you know,
kuya Aga and Andres...

148
00:07:07,048 --> 00:07:08,048
- are faultless…
- See?!

149
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:09,697
- They didn’t peep on you.
- There we go!

150
00:07:09,722 --> 00:07:11,834
I’ll take the blame, Kuya.
I’ll take it all.

151
00:07:12,221 --> 00:07:13,927
Let’s just say I’m the one
who peeped in on you!

152
00:07:14,462 --> 00:07:17,907
And while you were taking a shower,
you were wearing something red.

153
00:07:18,368 --> 00:07:19,741
No, it was maroon!

154
00:07:19,766 --> 00:07:20,865
- Andres?!
- Andres!

155
00:07:22,751 --> 00:07:24,824
Dad… no, it’s not like that!

156
00:07:24,849 --> 00:07:27,157
- I’m not bringing you to the-
- Stop talk-

157
00:07:27,658 --> 00:07:28,718
Aha!

158
00:07:29,457 --> 00:07:31,123
Look at you idiots!

159
00:07:31,499 --> 00:07:35,827
You really prioritized
drinking over closing my store!

160
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,891
Do you want me to handle all these alone?!

161
00:07:39,232 --> 00:07:40,232
What is this?!

162
00:07:40,408 --> 00:07:41,768
You made the uncooked rice your snacks?!

163
00:07:41,793 --> 00:07:43,880
Not everything crunchy
are peanuts to snack on!

164
00:07:44,131 --> 00:07:45,444
You pests!

165
00:07:49,689 --> 00:07:50,716
How rude!

166
00:07:51,224 --> 00:07:52,951
You talk like you’re beyond us!

167
00:07:53,313 --> 00:07:55,186
You look sickly!

168
00:07:55,253 --> 00:07:58,826
Not because you’re my boss…
I can easily replace you!

169
00:08:04,209 --> 00:08:05,209
This annoying person!

170
00:08:09,383 --> 00:08:10,410
I can feel my blood pressure rising!

171
00:08:15,035 --> 00:08:16,626
Boss Beauty,
what are you being so dramatic about,

172
00:08:16,650 --> 00:08:18,240
why haven’t you
closed your store yet?

173
00:08:18,529 --> 00:08:19,529
Ninong,

174
00:08:19,715 --> 00:08:22,108
thank you for helping me
make a way with the

175
00:08:22,132 --> 00:08:24,525
Captain so I can establish
my POGO business.

176
00:08:25,025 --> 00:08:26,025
Sssh!

177
00:08:26,918 --> 00:08:27,918
POGO?!

178
00:08:28,452 --> 00:08:29,452
That’s illegal!

179
00:08:29,477 --> 00:08:31,860
The president said so in his SONA
that POGOs are now illegal!

180
00:08:31,885 --> 00:08:33,047
This SONA, just recently!

181
00:08:34,378 --> 00:08:35,378
Be cautious!

182
00:08:35,664 --> 00:08:37,218
I know you’re going
to keep this to yourself.

183
00:08:37,686 --> 00:08:41,613
You should be the only
POGO operator here.

184
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:44,367
So don’t say anything like that!

185
00:08:44,846 --> 00:08:46,073
I’m sorry.

186
00:08:47,509 --> 00:08:49,457
I really don’t know how
those POGOs are able

187
00:08:49,481 --> 00:08:51,428
to establish when they
know they’re illegal!

188
00:08:51,453 --> 00:08:52,453
They really are!

189
00:08:53,413 --> 00:08:54,413
Someone’s at the door?

190
00:08:56,753 --> 00:08:57,753
There’s someone!

191
00:09:16,650 --> 00:09:17,837
POGO?!

192
00:09:18,163 --> 00:09:19,223
Yes, Kuya!

193
00:09:19,431 --> 00:09:20,938
Mariposa and I saw it
with our own eyes!

194
00:09:21,784 --> 00:09:25,197
That’s right.
We heard Chef K say…

195
00:09:26,025 --> 00:09:30,819
“Keep this to yourself, okay?
You should be the only POGO operator here.”

196
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:32,037
Something like that!

197
00:09:32,545 --> 00:09:34,645
It was his voice, I know it was!

198
00:09:34,789 --> 00:09:36,008
- Oh dear!
- Wow!

199
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,033
I never said such a thing!

200
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:41,176
Wait a minute, here we go again,
jumping to conclusions!

201
00:09:41,201 --> 00:09:42,825
No, wait, wait!

202
00:09:43,122 --> 00:09:47,780
If that’s indeed true, are we going
to let them establish a POGO hub here?

203
00:09:47,981 --> 00:09:51,551
Don’t bad things happen
in areas with those?

204
00:09:51,858 --> 00:09:52,858
That’s right!

205
00:09:52,944 --> 00:09:54,184
But, Lola,

206
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:59,328
it’s because of POGO that
I experienced my first kiss!

207
00:09:59,444 --> 00:10:00,444
Huh?!

208
00:10:00,469 --> 00:10:01,469
What is the connection?!

209
00:10:01,554 --> 00:10:04,109
Mm-mm, let me tell you a story.

210
00:10:04,134 --> 00:10:07,716
It was just last night,
and then he kissed-

211
00:10:07,741 --> 00:10:08,834
Alright, that’s enough!

212
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,486
I have to apologize for Mariposa.

213
00:10:12,951 --> 00:10:14,904
She’s really like this in the morning,
her brain is mush!

214
00:10:14,929 --> 00:10:17,788
It’s not only in the morning,
Boss Beauty!

215
00:10:18,456 --> 00:10:19,456
Ah,

216
00:10:19,956 --> 00:10:20,956
Mariposa,

217
00:10:21,692 --> 00:10:22,979
I just need to say this, okay?

218
00:10:30,103 --> 00:10:31,692
Did you know that

219
00:10:31,717 --> 00:10:33,764
a kiss is sweeter

220
